    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="1456"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1456">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/2116.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of the Navy</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Navy Department</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 22, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit herewith, for the
                    information of the Department of State, a copy of a cablegram, dated October
                    20th, 1912, received from the Commander-in-Chief, Pacific Fleet, at Corinto,
                    stating that, except the landing forces of <hi rend="italic">Cleveland</hi> and
                        <hi rend="italic">Denver</hi>, the force now in Nicaragua will be retained
                    on shore until the election of November 3rd, 1912.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beekman Winthrop.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commander-in-Chief, Pacific
                                Fleet</gloss>, to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss>
                        </hi>.</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Annapolis</hi>, <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Corinto</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-20">
                                <hi rend="italic">October 20, 1912</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Except the landing force of <hi rend="italic">Cleveland</hi> [and] <hi
                            rend="italic">Denver</hi>, will retain force on shore until election of
                        November 3, 1912; I do not anticipate any trouble, but consider it wise to
                        be prepared.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Southerland.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
